records.addlTxt:
Defendant Blair Ashley Adam in court with attorney Jessica Bellows.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction; STRAIGHT TIME; NO ELECTRONIC MONITORING.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS.
Conditions: 
*  Pay restitution in the amount of $2340.00 to David S., or if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Write of a letter of apology to David S.;
*  Maintain full time employment;
*  Perform 25 hours of community service;
*  Successfully complete a parenting class;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Serve 30 days in the House of Correction with release privileges for work; stayed until June 12, 2015 by 5:00 pm.
